expr ? action1 : action2
grade = (avg >= 65) ? "Pass" : "Fail"


for (set_counter; test_counter; increment_counter)
	action

set_counter: sets the initial value for a counter variable
test_counter: states a condition that is tested at the top of the loop
increment_counter: increments the counter each time at the bottom of the loop, right before testing the test_counter again

Below is an example that prints each field on the input line
	for (i = 1; i <= NF; i++)
		print $i


